SIMPLE: locket
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Locket
<hw>Lock"et</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>loquet</ets>
latch, dim. of OF. <ets>loc</ets> latch, lock; of German origin. See
<er>Lock</er> a fastening.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A small lock; a catch or spring to fasten a necklace
or other ornament.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A little case for holding a miniature picture or
lock of hair, usually suspended from a necklace or watch
chain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lock-gate</ent>⟦br⟧
